        "question": "What is the difference between MeSH Terms and MeSH Major Topic?",
        "answer": "MeSH Terms search for your concept anywhere in the article indexing. MeSH Major Topic limits results to articles where your concept is a primary focus, giving higher precision but potentially lower recall."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do I choose between Explode and No Explode?",
        "answer": "Explode includes the MeSH term and all its narrower terms in the hierarchy. Use Explode for comprehensive searches. Use No Explode when you only want articles about the exact concept, not its subtypes."
      },
      {
        "question": "Does this skill search PubMed automatically?",
        "answer": "No. This skill builds precise search query strings. You copy the output and paste it into the PubMed search box at pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov to execute the search."
